s"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"recjNRR60PAuFtjha","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"reccdFYIq50NyxNej","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"recqIoG1fkaNWJ1y0","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"recsU2ZSdzBvDqzgI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"reco82mzy0XTzaOgv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"recOZxrWd00qyF4Ej","label":"event"},{"source":"rec7c4225eIMb7UJd","target":"recmXmhZt51doQu7o","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recG97lop0P3JRiRE","ref":"Mark.12.1","text":"And he began to speak unto them by parables. A certain man planted a vineyard, and set an hedge about it, and digged a place for the winefat, and built a tower, and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country.","year":33},{"id":"rec1WSK4aSVubJrPm","ref":"Mark.12.2","text":"And at the season he sent to the husbandmen a servant, that he might receive from the husbandmen of the fruit of the vineyard.","year":33},{"id":"recu7wKyQYfsKrA1v","ref":"Mark.12.3","text":"And they caught him, and beat him, and sent him away empty.","year":33},{"id":"recAehQKE7lOyVynZ","ref":"Mark.12.4","text":"And again he sent unto them another servant; and at him they cast stones, and wounded him in the head, and sent him away shamefully handled.","year":33},{"id":"recv2parU2754stMO","ref":"Mark.12.5","text":"And again he sent another; and him they killed, and many others; beating some, and killing some.","year":33},{"id":"recxEJi2iZh8pv3RV","ref":"Mark.12.6","text":"Having yet therefore one son, his wellbeloved, he sent him also last unto them, saying, They will reverence my son.","year":33},{"id":"recNEMBJClLsjB7Nv","ref":"Mark.12.7","text":"But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours.","year":33},{"id":"recU9vkhJ0mMWkarG","ref":"Mark.12.8","text":"And they took him, and killed him, and cast him out of the vineyard.","year":33}]}
